<div class="quote-controls"></div>
<img loading="lazy" alt="" width="24" height="24" src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/a/0ea827/48.png" class="avatar"> atsekhan:</div>
<blockquote>
<p>what does this coefficient do exactly?</p>
</blockquote>
</aside>
<p>The coefficient is just multiplied by the sensor value. <a href="https://docs.ctre-phoenix.com/en/latest/ch16_ClosedLoop.html#closedloop-configurations" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">See the docs</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Scalar (0,1] to multiply selected sensor value before using.<br>
Note this will reduce resolution of the closed-loop.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>As <a href="https://docs.ctre-phoenix.com/en/latest/ch14a_BringUpRemoteSensors.html#bring-up-the-sensor-on-the-remote-ctre-can-device" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">noted in the docs</a>, when a pigeon is the remote sensor it uses native units. 360-degrees is 8192 units. If you want to work with degrees you can use the coefficient, or do the math in your code. But, it seems to me you’d want 360.0/8192.0, not 3600.0/8192.0, but I may be missing something.</p>","post_number":4,"post_type":1,"posts_count":44,"updated_at":"2022-12-05T06:26:48.863Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":3,"quote_count":1,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":208,"readers_count":207,"score":61.6,"yours":false,"topic_id":419195,"topic_slug":"motionmagic-hardware-pid-turning","display_username":"Andy Gasser","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.ctre-phoenix.com/en/latest/ch16_ClosedLoop.html#closedloop-configurations","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Motor Controller Closed Loop — Phoenix documentation","clicks":2},{"url":"https://docs.ctre-phoenix.com/en/latest/ch14a_BringUpRemoteSensors.html#bring-up-the-sensor-on-the-remote-ctre-can-device","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Bring Up: Remote Sensors — Phoenix documentation","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":44380,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/motionmagic-hardware-pid-turning/419195/4","custom_user_title":"7028 - Java Programming Mentor","reactions":[{"id":"heart","typ