<p>Just encoders wouldn’t work very well if you want to spin in place to a specific heading. It’s difficult to predict how the wheels will scrub. A common way to do it is in robot code with a PIDController or ProfiledPIDController. <a href="https://github.com/STMARobotics/frc-7028-2022/blob/master/src/main/java/frc/robot/commands/autonomous/TurnToAngleCommand.java" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Here’s our turn-to-angle command</a> from 2022.</p>
